com.singularityeye.eyetrack

Class BoundService

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.content.Context
      • android.content.ContextWrapper
        • android.app.Service
          • com.singularityeye.eyetrack.BoundService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2

    public class BoundService
extends android.app.Service
    BoundService model is a Service that includes a single background task/thread to execute soap requests and send local broadcasts (actions) to client.
    Version:
    1.0.0-alpha
    Author:
    Manuel Martin-Gonzalez

      • initTask

        public void initTask(java.lang.String id,
                     java.lang.String ip,
                     java.lang.String seconds,
                     java.lang.String key)
        Create new task/thread. It starts sending soap requests, and sending local broadcasts (actions) to client.
        Parameters:
        id - string that identifies the platform
        ip - android device ip
        seconds - the last seconds for what we get the positions
        key - string that holds the soap web service license key

      • stopTask

        public void stopTask()
        Stop the main task/thread. It stops sending soap requests, and sending local broadcasts (actions) to client.
